# Summary
This documentation page explains SDK Middleware in Amplitude, a feature that allows developers to extend functionality by running custom code on every event for enrichment, transformation, filtering, and routing. It details the middleware structure, function signature, payload customization, and provides examples for filtering events, removing PII, enriching properties, and forwarding data to other services.

